name: Claw of the Crescent Moon
description: When a body is discovered at daybreak with three deep rents down its back, authorities know to leave well enough alone.

name: Crystal Fist
description: A diamond is harder than bone, and it’s happy to prove it.

name: Cursed Unguis
description: Long ago a forgotten warrior made a dark bargain, trading flesh for power. This is all that remains.

name: Deadfang
description: Late at night, when the world is quiet and still, you can faintly hear it pleading for its next meal.

name: Emerald Talons
description: Not all craftsmen work the loom or potter’s wheel. The Balak Taw know - violence too is an art.

name: Gossamer Gauntlets
description: With steel spun fine as a spider’s thread, these blades rip wounds as gaping as a bear's bite.

name: Gutterpig
description: The Boarskin deliberately leave their blades uncleaned. Infection leads to rot, and rot leads to victory .

name: Ironstud Interrogators
description: The Knights of Tanth popularized this design for both open combat and backroom “questioning”. Answers tend to dislodge as fast as teeth.

name: Nith Grovebinders
description: Wood rots, cloth frays, stone crumbles, but fury smolders eternal.

name: Reibach's Claws
description: It cuts as clean as a surgeon’s scalpel, only its patients rarely recover.

name: Shellguard Gauntlets
description: One step above tying rocks to your fists - these gloves are meant to pulp and pulverize. Grace is for dancers.

name: Sun's Scorn
description: Some say the sun is fueled by fire. Others insist it’s rage.

name: Swamp Nail
description: War is messy. Why shouldn’t one’s injuries be the same?

name: The Dawn Never Comes
description: Cerim texts contain no reference to a life after the Pestilence is gone.

name: Woven Wraps
description: Simple cloth wraps for those who trust that their fists are plenty hard enough.

name: Bandit's Cleaver
description: A heavy iron axe carried often by bandits, and a testament to the fact that not all threats are hollow.

name: Boarskin Reaper
description: There is no piece of nature's bounty and grace that the Boarskin can't defile.

name: Broken Fang
description: A shattered axe, having long since left pieces of itself buried in skulls and rib cages, but still deadly.

name: Cerim's Skyrend
description: Those who can no longer hear the Sayer over the howl of their own madness should be pitied. Pitied and feared.

name: Gilded Twibill
description: "Paint your axe gold, so that your enemies may mistake the shine in their skull for heaven." - old proverb

name: Harvester's Dread
description: Before being twisted into Harvesters, many woodsmen would set camp for their families near the forest. Hence the oldest blood on their axes.

name: Huro's Great Axe
description: In the legend of Huro, he used his axe to fell an entire forest, as well as the minor god he angered in doing so.

name: Midnight Shredder
description: Not all great axes are graceless, brutal weapons. But this one is.

name: Short Bardiche
description: It's considered a sign of respect from the Riders of Langold if they face you with the longer of twin axe faces.

name: Spalled Axe
description: The Dasha people of Marin eschew weapons, but their sturdy axes don't care how they're put to use.

name: Brutish Cudgel
description: It's an ongoing debate as to whether giants ever roamed the land. Clubs such as these keep the question open.

name: Evening Star
description: No dawn follows the blow of an Evening Star.

name: Fetid Club
description: As one counts the years ringed on a tree trunk, one can count the lives smeared on this massive staff.

name: Paddle
description: A massive paddle.

name: Bud of the Everlasting Tree
description: A strange growth cut from a holy tree - it continues to grow with each swing, as if fed by blood.

name: Cinder & Stone
description: Studded with small, strange faces, it's said to be the burial tool for a long lost hill tribe.

name: Festering Cleft
description: A sickly stone affixed to a shaft. Perhaps it will shatter tomorrow. Perhaps never.

name: Pound of Cadavers
description: The blood, bones, and flesh of fallen warriors woven into a grotesque amalgamation.

name: Spliced Hammer
description: Originally designed for shattering unruly stones, it seems to take greater pleasure doing the same to skulls.

name: Tooth of the Ancient One
description: The tooth of an unknown monstrosity. With any luck, its owner is no longer searching for it.

name: Weeping Earth
description: A tree trunk forms a crude but effective mallet, used by those Risen raiders weighty enough to lift it.

name: Blister
description: It's said that if a shard of this jagged sword chips off, it will grow in its victim's body, turning their blood to iron.

name: Claymore
description: A remnant of simpler times, when one knight faced another in an open field.

name: Corpse Smeared Blade
description: Previously wielded by a plagued monstrosity, no amount of scrubbing seems able to remove the stench.

name: Falstead's Fury
description: This towering blade seems heavy with memory - battles won and lost and never fought.

name: Festering Earth
description: A long buried blade, chewed away by the elements, dragged out of its grave for one final campaign.

name: Freiheit
description: A weapon made famous from its use by freedom fighters during the Monksbane Wars.

name: Gnarled Saw
description: If its first swing doesn't sever a limb, a few back and forth motions will do the trick.

name: Icebreaker
description: Used in winter to shear off great blocks of ice, it finds other uses year round.

name: Mayhem
description: The brutal, massive blade of an executioner who has lost their purpose but not their calling.

name: Shattered Sun
description: A design that saw great popularity in Phalen until its designer was caught in bed with the King's nephew.

name: Sieger
description: Stamped with the seal of the great smith Tomlin the Third, its blade will cut a falling feather in two.

name: Summer's Sting
description: The knights of Elgarth test their blade's edge by counting the stalks of wheat they can fell in a single swing.

name: Bolein Polearm
description: Few sights are more intimidating than a sea of Bolein knights, each hoisting their phoenix beak aloft.

name: Regal Cleft
description: It's tradition for an apprenticing mainland knight to choose the stone to serve as his halberd's counterweight.

name: Serrated Cutter
description: A grisly polearm carried often by Havenport guards - Governor Grafston's idea of "justice with teeth."

name: Hope Shorn
description: The scythe of The Reapers - a sadistic death cult - this unholy weapon whispers a dark thirst.

name: Scythe of Wretches
description: Before the pestilence rotted their minds and limbs, the Nith used such scythes to harvest swampgrass roots.

name: Soul Thresher
description: "Easy to separate a head from a neck, far harder to separate a soul from a body." - Thorn executioner axiom

name: Caretaker's Ruined Staff
description: A Dasha Caretaker's staff, only grown putrid and diseased. Lulling voices can almost be heard wafting from it.

name: Cursed Crone
description: Some say witches still lurk in Sacra's dark corners, crafting tools out of wood, mold, and unlucky creatures.

name: Advancing Flurry
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Advancing Flurry</color> Rune Attack.

Advance while unleashing a rapid flurry of strikes, pushing back enemies with each hit.

name: Air Dodge
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Air Dodge</color> Rune Attack.

Execute an aerial roll to evade attacks, then immediately counter with a swift, forward stab.

name: Armageddon
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Wand</color> or a <color=#F2E6BD>Staff</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Armageddon</color> Rune Attack.

Call down a devastating inferno in front of you, engulfing the area in a massive explosion of fire.

name: Arrowstorm
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Bow</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Arrowstorm</color> Rune Attack.

Fire a lone arrow skyward, calling down a punishing rain of arrows that showers the battlefield and overwhelms foes caught beneath it.

name: Balance Smash
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Two-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Balance Smash</color> Rune Attack.

Balance atop your weapon as you roll over it, then seize it firmly to deliver a ground-shattering smash.

name: Bare Knuckle
description:
Slot this Rune into <color=#F2E6BD>Gauntlets</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Bare Knuckle</color> Rune Attack.

Wind up and lunge forward with explosive force, delivering a powerful punch that knocks enemies clean off their feet.

name: Berserk Flurry
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Two-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Berserk Flurry</color> Rune Attack.

Channel the fury of a berserker and surge forward, unleashing four rapid, powerful swings to overwhelm your foes.

name: Berserk Strike
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Two-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Berserk Strike</color> Rune Attack.

Thump your chest to fuel your rage, then deliver a devastating strike that crushes the enemy with brutal force.

name: Blazing Rupture
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Blazing Rupture</color> Rune Attack.

Smash your weapon into the ground to create a fiery explosion, then spin in a searing arc to strike nearby enemies with burning force.

name: Blink
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Utility Slot</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Blink</color> Spell.

Harness mystical energy to teleport forward a short distance, even passing through enemies to evade or position strategically.

name: Bolt
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Staff</color> or a <color=#F2E6BD>Wand</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Bolt</color> Rune Attack.

Cast a crackling lightning bolt that electrifies enemies on impact. Charge it to increase its shocking power and deal more damage.

name: Breaker Thrust
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Two-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Breaker Thrust</color> Rune Attack.

Lunge forward with overwhelming force, thrusting your weapon into enemies to knock them off their feet.

name: Breakrush
description:
Slot this Rune into <color=#F2E6BD>Gauntlets</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Breakrush</color> Rune Attack.

Unleash a barrage of quick strikes in rapid succession, pummeling your opponent with relentless blows.

name: Breakstep
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Bow</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Breakstep</color> Rune Attack.

Drive a sharp kick into your foe, then follow through with three rapid arrows before they can recover.

name: Brutal Reprise
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Brutal Reprise</color> Rune Attack.

Swing your weapon in a brutal flourish, then unleash three heavy strikes in rapid succession to overpower your enemy.

name: Buster Rift
description:
Slot this Rune into <color=#F2E6BD>Gauntlets</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Buster Rift</color> Technique.

Deliver a ground-tearing punch that launches a tremor wave forward, then slide back and fire a second explosive strike.

name: Chain Lightning
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Staff</color> or a <color=#F2E6BD>Wand</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Chain Lightning</color> Rune Attack.

Unleash a lightning bolt that strikes your target and, when charged, arcs to hit additional nearby enemies, electrifying the battlefield.

name: Channel
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Utility Slot</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Channel</color> Spell.

Charge this spell to draw in sacred energy, sacrificing health to gain focus and amplify your mystical power.

name: Charge Strike
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Charge Strike</color> Rune Attack.

Charge forward with lethal momentum, culminating in a brutal strike that devastates any foe in your path.

name: Charged Bolt
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Wand</color> or a <color=#F2E6BD>Staff</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Charged Bolt</color> Rune Attack.

Release bolts of lightning in all directions, shocking nearby enemies with surging energy.

name: Arrow
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Bow</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Arrow</color> Rune Attack.

A fundamental archer’s skill, release a swift and precise arrow aimed straight at the heart of your adversary.

name: Circular
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>One-Handed Weapon</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Circular</color> Rune Attack.

Execute a swift spin, striking enemies twice with a powerful circular attack that hits all around you.

name: Cold Affliction
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Utility Slot</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Cold Affliction</color> Spell.

Envelop enemies in biting frost, increasing the ice damage and freeze buildup they receive for a short duration.

name: Cold Enchantment
description:
Slot this Rune into a <color=#F2E6BD>Utility Slot</color> to gain the <color=#F2E6BD>Cold Enchantment</color> Spell.

Infuse your weapon with the essence of cold, chilling foes with frosty strikes that slow their advance.
